Random Variables 

Binomial distribution 
X ~ Bin(n,p)
1) Story : n independent trials, p is the probability of success,X is the number of success. 
2) Sum of indicator variables X=X1+X2+...+Xn. Xj=1 if success,or 0 if fail. X1,X2,...,Xn are i.i.d= independent identically distribution.
3) PMF. probability mass function (only for discrete variables: possibe values a1,a2,.... can be listed out) 
P(X=k) = (n,k)p^k q^(n-k) 
P(X=aj)=pj for all j.pj >= 0 ; sum_j pj=1 

CDF F(x)=P(X<=x) : cumulative distribution function 
